This paper proposes an efficient fully convolutional neural network (CNN) image dehazing method, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also explores different model designs and parameter counts, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GPUs for real-time systems, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes benchmarks and performance evaluations, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
